TITLE: Creating a Basic Forest Admin Agent with SQL Data Source
DESCRIPTION: Example of how to create a simple Forest Admin agent with a SQL data source. The code initializes the agent, adds a SQL data source, customizes schema, and starts the agent on port 3310.
SOURCE: https://github.com/forestadmin/agent-nodejs/blob/main/packages/plugin-aws-s3/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createAgent } from '@forestadmin/agent';
import { createSqlDataSource } from '@forestadmin/datasource-sql';

// Create your Forest Admin agent
const agent = createAgent({
  authSecret: process.env.FOREST_AUTH_SECRET,
  envSecret: process.env.FOREST_ENV_SECRET,
  isProduction: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production',
});

// Create and add a datasource to your agent
agent.addDataSource(createSqlDataSource({
  uri: process.env.DATABASE_URL,
}));

// Add customizations here

// Launch your Forest Admin agent
agent.mountOnStandaloneServer(3310).start();
```

