TITLE: Nested Promise Chain with Resource Cleanup in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This pattern demonstrates handling nested promise chains where a resource is created, used, and then properly disposed. The outer chain ensures resource cleanup occurs regardless of success or failure in the inner operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/forestadmin/agent-nodejs/blob/main/packages/datasource-sequelize/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function operationWithCleanup() {
  // Create some resource
  const resource = await createResource();

  // Use promise chain to ensure cleanup
  return Promise.resolve()
    .then(async () => {
      // Do something with the resource that may throw or return a rejected promise
      const result = await doSomethingWithResource(resource);

      // Do more operations that depend on the previous step
      return doMoreOperations(result);
    })
    .finally(() => cleanupResource(resource));
}
```

