TITLE: Creating and Managing Resources with Promise Chains in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates a pattern for creating temporary resources that need to be properly cleaned up regardless of whether the operation succeeds or fails. It uses promise chaining to ensure proper resource disposal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/forestadmin/agent-nodejs/blob/main/packages/datasource-sequelize/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class ResourceManager {
  async createResource() {
    // Create a temporary resource
    const resource = await this.setupResource();

    // Return a chain that will always clean up the resource
    return Promise.resolve()
      .then(() => this.useResource(resource))
      .finally(() => this.cleanupResource(resource));
  }

  async setupResource() {
    // Implementation of resource creation
  }

  async useResource(resource) {
    // Use the resource for something
  }

  async cleanupResource(resource) {
    // Clean up the resource
  }
}
```

